R1:
vacuuming is disruptive to people and animals, and for some animals, is actively scary.  It is generally not a good idea to scare the animals.  Best to do that when they aren't there.  

Mopping is also an issue; people or animals walking on wet floors can fall and get hurt, or just track extra dirt that's harder to get up than it would be if the floor were dry.  Also, doesn't make a lot of sense to mop while people or animals are milling about, because it would ruin the work as soon as it was done.  

It's obviously great to carry food and drinks to people, and even animals, who are there.  Circulate and offer refreshment as desired, yay!  Or to carry it past them to a table (or from a table if they're done eating) is also fine.  

I don't think it matters much one way or another if the robot is carrying stuff past people or animals, as long as it is smart enough not to hit people with the stuff as the robot goes by.  

And picking up stuff could be fairly unobtrusive.  I've seen human maids and janitors picking stuff up while people are doing their thing; it's no big deal.
R2: Literally the same reasons as before.  Nothing has changed, except that the potential to scare animals isn't relevant this time.
R4: Nothing changes... (also, I cannot see this image)
R6:
Nothing has changed.
